comment.author: 25453448@N02
comment._content: As in your tag, this is in the county of Dorset (or Dorsetshire in older times). Durdle Door is probably one of the most famous landmarks in Dorset. The Dorset coast is outstanding and almost entirely unspoilt. Outside the conurbation of Bournemouth-Poole at its eastern end, the whole of it, together with that of neighbouring East Devon is now a UNESCO World Heritage Site called the Jurassic Coast.
